httpHeaderAddressList: --- AddressList parses the named header field as a list of addresses.
httpHeaderDate: --- Date parses the Date header field.
httpHeaderGet:
--- Get gets the first value associated with the given key.
--- It is case insensitive; CanonicalMIMEHeaderKey is used
--- to canonicalize the provided key.
--- If there are no values associated with the key, Get returns "".
--- To access multiple values of a key, or to use non-canonical keys,
--- access the map directly.
mailAddressParserParse:
--- Parse parses a single RFC 5322 address of the
--- form "Gogh Fir <gf@example.com>" or "foo@example.com".
mailAddressParserParseList:
--- ParseList parses the given string as a list of comma-separated addresses
--- of the form "Gogh Fir <gf@example.com>" or "foo@example.com".
mailAddressString:
--- String formats the address as a valid RFC 5322 address.
--- If the address's name contains non-ASCII characters
--- the name will be rendered according to RFC 2047.
mailParseAddress: --- ParseAddress parses a single RFC 5322 address, e.g. "Barry Gibbs <bg@example.com>"
mailParseAddressList: --- ParseAddressList parses the given string as a list of addresses.
mailParseDate: --- ParseDate parses an RFC 5322 date string.
mailReadMessage:
--- ReadMessage reads a message from r.
--- The headers are parsed, and the body of the message will be available
--- for reading from msg.Body.
